Dorothy DOWNEY, as Administratrix of the Estate of James P. Downey, Deceased, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. VICTORY CARRIERS, Inc., Defendant-Appellant. No. 192, Docket 24818. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued April 11, 1958. Decided April 11, 1958. Hill, Betts & Nash, New York City (Robert S. Blanc, Jr., New York City, on the brief), for defendant-appellant. Klein & Ruderman, New York City ■ (Harvey Goldstein, New York City, on the brief), for plaintiff-appellee.

Before SWAN, HINCKS and MOORE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed in open court for lack of appellate jurisdiction.
